headline_main: Security Clearance, Chicago, Nipsey Hussle: Your Tuesday Briefing

snippet: The former vice president has been accused of inappropriate touching by a female politician in Nevada. Colbert got into the awkward details of those claims.
lead_paragraph: Welcome to Best of Late Night, a rundown of the previous night’s highlights that lets you sleep — and lets us get paid to watch comedy. abstract: The former vice president has been accused of inappropriate touching by a female politician in Nevada. Colbert got into the awkward details of those claims.

snippet: He’s not a sexual predator, but he is out of touch.
lead_paragraph: On Friday, Lucy Flores, a former Democratic candidate for lieutenant governor of Nevada, accused Joe Biden of touching her inappropriately as they waited to take the stage at a 2014 election rally. He put his hands on her shoulders, she said, then nuzzled her hair and kissed the back of her head. She didn’t accuse Biden, who is reportedly close to announcing his presidential candidacy, of sexual harassment or assault, just of making her uncomfortable. “I’m not suggesting that Biden broke any laws, but the transgressions that society deems minor (or doesn’t even see as transgressions) often feel considerable to the person on the receiving end,” she wrote.
abstract: He’s not a sexual predator, but he is out of touch.

headline_main: The Wrong Time for Joe Biden

snippet: A Connecticut woman, Amy Lappos, said Mr. Biden rubbed noses with her at a fund-raiser in 2009. Mr. Biden’s past behavior has been misrepresented, a spokesman for him said.
lead_paragraph: A second woman on Monday accused Joseph R. Biden Jr. of touching her in a way that made her feel uncomfortable, intensifying the scrutiny of the former vice president’s close physical interactions with women over the years as he prepares for a likely presidential bid.
